pytest . # run tests from current directory
pytest tests/test_gist.py # run tests from specific folder
-v[vv] # verbose
-p no:warnings # disable warnings
--disable-warnings # disable warnings
-s # print output (don't capture it)
-k <keywords_here> # filter by keyword
-m <marker> # filter by marker
-m "not <marker>" # leave out the marked tests
pytest --fixtures # show fixtures (from pytest and user created) 
pytest <testing_module> --cov-report [term-missing or html] --cov <tested_module> # coverage report
# pragma: no cover # exclude block of code from coverage report

-----------------------------------------------------------------------
python -m unittest [<file>] [Options]

Coverage in unittest:
1) python -m coverage run -m unittest
2) python -m coverage